http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/KIA-sees-25.2-per-cent-growth-in-2015/article14009913.ece

Kempegowda International Airport clocked 18 million passengers and recorded a 25.2 per cent growth in overall traffic during 2015, compared to the corresponding period in 2014.This comes a year after the airport clocked 15 million passengers in 2014.“This shows we are closer to our long-term goals of becoming a gateway to the southern region,” said G.V. Sanjay Reddy, Managing Director, BIAL.During 2015, the domestic passenger traffic showed a growth of 27.4 per cent compared with the previous year, while international passenger traffic grew at 15.8 per cent compared with the same period.BIAL, in a communique, claimed: “On time Performance (OTP) touched 88 per cent and remained above 84 per cent for most part of the year.”KIA clocked 63,769 passengers on December 4, 2015, making it the highest single day traffic since the start of airport operations.The new passenger details reveal that on an average 50,500 passengers are served by KIA everyday.The busiest domestic routes are Delhi, Mumbai and Pune.The airport saw some new services added to Jodhpur, Maurai, Rajkot and Cuddapah in the domestic arena, while new international routes to San Francisco, Kathmandu and Kuwait were also added.The cargo operations also expanded by 5.4 per cent during 2015, reaching a total volume of 2.87 lakh tonnes.New cargo services to Addis Ababa was introduced in the year increasing the freighter connectivity to West Asia.Kempegowda InternationalAirport clocks18 million passengers